<div type="definition">
<p>Something GOOD that IS USEFUL TO THE ONE WHO HAS IT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for any kind of material or other profit or advantage is yì 益 (ant. sǔn 損 "loss").</p>
<p>2. Lì 利 (1. ant. yì 義 "considerations of rectitude"(!!); 2. ant. hài 害 "damage and loss suffered") refers to material profit.</p>
<p>3. Dé 得 (ant. shī 失 "lose") refers abstractly to what is achieved as a desired advantage.</p>
<p>5. Rù 入 (ant. chū 出 "expense") is manifest material gain.</p>
<p>6. Biàn 便 (ant. zǔ 阻 "hindrance and disadvantage") refers to a convenient adantage.</p>
        </div>
